TY  - JOUR
AU  - Llorente, Guillermo
AU  - Michaely, Roni
AU  - Saar, Gideon
AU  - Wang, Jiang
T1  - Dynamic Volume-Return Relation of Individual Stocks
PY  - 2002
Y1  - 2002/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/15.4.1005
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 15
IS  - 4
SP  - 1005
EP  - 1047
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We examine the dynamic relation between return and volume of individual stocks. Using a simple model in which investors trade to share risk or speculate on private information, we show that returns generated by risk-sharing trades tend to reverse themselves, while returns generated by speculative trades tend to continue themselves. We test this theoretical prediction by analyzing the relation between daily volume and first-order return autocorrelation for individual stocks listed on the NYSE and AMEX. We find that the cross-sectional variation in the relation between volume and return autocorrelation is related to the extent of informed trading in a manner consistent with the theoretical prediction.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/15.4.1005
ER  - 



